title: Moore, Lynx Beat Buzzer in WNBA Finals
text:
Moore, Lynx Beat Buzzer in WNBA Finals 
By Zach Schneider Moore, Lynx Beat Buzzer in WNBA Finals October 9, 2015 Updated Oct 9, 2015 at 10:44 PM CDT 
Indianapolis, IN (NNCNOW.com) --- Maya Moore hit a game-winning three-pointer as time expired on Friday night, giving the Minnesota Lynx an 80-77 win over the Indiana Fever in game three of the WNBA Finals. 
Moore led all scorers in the game with 24 points, including that game-winning three that came off an inbounds play with 1.7 seconds left. 
Minnesota also got 13 points from Seimone Augustus and 12 from Renee Montgomery, who hit a three-pointer with just over a minute left to tie the game at 77-77. 
The Lynx now lead the best-of-five series 2-1, with game four set for Sunday at 7:30 p.m.
